Tension is mounting in Mitchells Plain with stones being hurled at police. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Angry residents in Mitchells Plain have clashed with police over food parcels. Residents are hungry and furious with the Social Development department for not fulfilling its promise of delivering food parcels to them. Residents hurled stones at police and vowed to stay on the streets until they are given the food parcels. READ: Sebokeng residents desperate for water - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.